Citation.sTitle: Density, Viscosity, Excess Molar Volume, and Viscosity Deviation of Three Amyl Alcohols + Ethanol Binary Mixtures from 293.15 to 323.15 K
Citation.sAbstract: Density and kinematic viscosity of (2-methyl-1-butanol + ethanol), (2-methyl-2-butanol + ethanol), and (3-methyl-1-butanol + ethanol) binary solutions were measured over the entire composition range and at seven different temperatures (293.15, 298.15, 303.15, 308.15, 313.15, 318.15, and 323.15) K, at atmospheric pressure. Redlich-Kister-type polynomial equations were used to fit the calculated excess molar volumes and viscosity deviations.
Citation.sKeyword: Density and kinematic viscosity of (2-methyl-1-butanol + ethanol)
